, 
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD2FFB2E7D1A329B0DA32EB" box="[424,467,1655,1679]" captionStart="FIGURES 125–128" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1082,1105]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-55@71.[233,1354,193,1061]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 125–128. Diagrams with distribution records for: 125, Debilos dialeucor sp. nov.; 126, D. dnopheror sp. nov.; 127, D. palaior sp. nov.; 128, D. soror (Trentepohl)." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">127</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFD2FFB2E6EEA3E7B1D93305" blockId="33.[151,1436,1721,2034]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFD2FFB2E6EEA3E7B02132B5" box="[151,296,1721,1746]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFD2FFB2E6EEA3E7B02832B6" bold="true" box="[151,289,1721,1746]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Female. Fore wing 
<quantity id="49035F81FFD2FFB2E46EA3E7B37A32B5" box="[535,627,1721,1745]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="9.8">9.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFD2FFB2E4F8A3E7B3B432B5" box="[641,701,1721,1745]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Head</emphasis>
: Antenna with 30–31 flagellomeres. Clypeus entirely punctate, smooth towards apex, markedly convex, most prominent ventrally, CWH 1.64; MWC 0.67, MLW 1.77, MWW 0.55; malar space moderately long, MSM 1.20; supra-antennal area with almost indistinct, median, longitudinal carina; minimum distance from eye margin to occipital carina laterally approximately same width of mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFD2FFB1E6BEA230B5EB3673" blockId="33.[151,1436,1721,2034]" lastBlockId="34.[151,1437,151,1580]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFD2FFB2E6BEA230B03633E1" box="[199,319,1902,1925]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFD2FFB2E6BEA230B03633E1" box="[199,319,1902,1925]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Mesosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD2FFB2E72CA233B0A633E1" box="[341,431,1901,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="64.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[198,1388,193,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-95@64.[198,1388,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. ♀. 91, 92, Debilos soror (Trentepohl), Holotype. 91, dorsal. 92, lateral. 93–95, lateral. 93, D. palaior sp. nov., BMNH. 94, D. dialeucor sp. nov., Holotype. 95, D. dnopheror sp. nov. Specimen from Brazil, PA, Melgaço, Floresta Nacional de Caxiuanã, 18–21.ix.2003 (UFES). Illustrations not to scale. Figs 91, 92 and 95 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
). Pronotum lateral portion distinctly strigate to rugose, epomia moderately marked; notaulus moderately impressed, inconspicuously, minutely corrugated, especially anteriorly, reaching about middle of mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD2FFB2E72AA2EBB0A133A9" box="[339,424,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–48" captionStartId="60.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,153,1890]" captionTargetId="figure-130@60.[209,1377,153,1890]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURES 41–48. Holotypes, ♀. 41–44, mesoscutum, dorsal. 41, Debilos okarum sp. nov. 42, D. typurum sp. nov. 43, D. palaior sp. nov. 44, D. dnopheror sp. nov. 45, 46, median portion of postpectal carina (arrow), mesothoracic venter, frontal. 45, D. masipum sp. nov. 46, D. sanimum sp. nov. 47, 48, epicnemial carina, mesopleuron, frontal, arrow: carina dorsal end. 47, D. okum sp. nov. 48, D. owinum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron dorsal half medially strigulate, ventral half posteriorly strigate with ridges taking mesopleural groove, epicnemial carina restricted to ventral 0.8 of mesopleuron, posteriorly inconspicuously, densely corrugated; mesopleural groove markedly, sparsely corrugated; sternaulus entirely markedly corrugated; postpectal carina medially distinctly bent; metapleuron, subapical fovea shallow, subcircular; pleural carina stout; propodeum anterior area short, PLL 0.48, anterior transverse carina distinct, complete, medially distinctly arched forwards (
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD1FFB1E769A45AB0613578" box="[272,360,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1901,1924]" captionTargetBox="[222,1364,155,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-118@56.[222,1364,155,1888]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. Propodeum posterior area, dorsal, ♀. 7, Debilos soror (Trentepohl), Holotype. 8, D. orthum sp. nov., Holotype. 9, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 10, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 11, D. palaior sp. nov., Holotype. 12, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 13, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 14, D. frater sp. nov., Holotype. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 7 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), posterior area markedly strigate-rugose, with ridges medially slightly arched backwards, spiracle very elongate, SWL 2.88 (
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD1FFB1E462A479B364355B" box="[539,621,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–58" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1277,1300]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-153@61.[151,1435,193,1256]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 49–58. ♀. 49, 50, propodeum, dorsal, Holotypes. 49, Debilos masipum sp. nov. 50, D. sanimum sp. nov. 51–53, metapleuron apical fovea (arrow), metapleuron, frontal. 51, D. soror (Trentepohl), Holotype. 52, D. dnopheror sp. nov., Holotype. 53, D. frater sp. nov., Holotype. 54–58, propodeal spiracle, frontal. 54, D. palaior sp. nov., Holotype. 55, D. dialeucor sp. nov., Holotype. 56, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 57, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 58, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 63 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), propodeal apophyses short, conical, AHD 1.43. Legs: Hind t4 posterior lobe about 0.75 × as long as anterior lobe. Wings (
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD1FFB1E4B1A412B2153500" box="[712,796,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-153@58.[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. ♀. 25, Debilos palaior sp. nov., fore wing, dorsal. Specimen from Ecuador, Morona-Santiago, Cordillera de Cutucú, 28.III.1981 (BMNH). 26–28, fore and hind wings, dorsal, Holotypes. 26, D. soror (Trentepohl). 27, D. orthum sp. nov. 28, D. frater sp. nov., arrow: ramellus. 29, hind wing, dorsal, D. curtuvenatum sp. nov., Holotype. 30–33, fore and hind wings, dorsal. 30, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 31, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 32, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 33, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 26 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
): Fore wing vein (Rs+M)b slightly but uniformly curved, limit with crossvein 1m-cu indistinct, ramellus absent; vein Rs&amp;1M posteriorly slightly curved; crossvein 1cu-a uniformly slightly convex, arising opposite vein Rs&amp;1M, angle with vein M+Cu about 90 degrees; vein 2Cua moderately shorter than crossvein 2cu-a, FWC 0.72; areolet small, APH 0.84; vein 2Ma distinctly longer than vein 2Mb; vein 2Mb tubular; crossvein 2m-cu with bulla short, about 0.2 × as long as vein length or shorter; vein 2Rsb sinuous. Hind wing vein 2-1A long, reaching about 0.8 × the distance to wing margin, HWC 1.72.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFD1FFB1E6BEA77BB5C836A8" blockId="34.[151,1437,151,1580]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFD1FFB1E6BEA77BB0353658" box="[199,316,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD1FFB1E735A77AB0A93658" box="[332,416,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–95" captionStartId="64.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[198,1388,193,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-95@64.[198,1388,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURES 91–95. ♀. 91, 92, Debilos soror (Trentepohl), Holotype. 91, dorsal. 92, lateral. 93–95, lateral. 93, D. palaior sp. nov., BMNH. 94, D. dialeucor sp. nov., Holotype. 95, D. dnopheror sp. nov. Specimen from Brazil, PA, Melgaço, Floresta Nacional de Caxiuanã, 18–21.ix.2003 (UFES). Illustrations not to scale. Figs 91, 92 and 95 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
). T1 petiole basal half smooth towards base, apical half, postpetiole coriarious-punctulate, except pospetiole apical parts centrally smooth, sparsely punctulate, spiracle at about basal 0.6, inconspicuously prominent, T1LW 3.17, T1WW 2.61, T1GL 0.32; T2 moderately short, apically robust, T2T1L 0.74, thyridium subcircular, T2LW 1.09, T2WW 1.93. Ovipositor slightly but uniformly downcurved, OST 0.69, dorsal valve with nodus faint, notch present; ventral valve tip with inconspicuous serrations restricted to very tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFD1FFB1E6BEA786B49437C0" blockId="34.[151,1437,151,1580]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFD1FFB1E6BEA786B00E3694" box="[199,263,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Color</emphasis>
. Head, mesosoma, legs and metasoma black. Head: Dorsal portion of flagellomeres 5–9 and mouth parts, except mandible, white. 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFD1FFB1E7C0A7A2B3B13770" authority=": Propodeal" authorityName="Propodeal" box="[441,696,764,788]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma: Propodeal</taxonomicName>
apophyses white. Legs: Trochanters apical margin white; fore femur anteriorly whitish towards apex; fore and mid tibiae anteriorly and posteriorly pale yellow (222, 194, 099); fore and mid tarsomeres brownish (180, 104, 061). Wings: With uniform yellowish tint (
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFD1FFB1E2F4A61AB5EB3738" box="[1165,1250,836,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-153@58.[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. ♀. 25, Debilos palaior sp. nov., fore wing, dorsal. Specimen from Ecuador, Morona-Santiago, Cordillera de Cutucú, 28.III.1981 (BMNH). 26–28, fore and hind wings, dorsal, Holotypes. 26, D. soror (Trentepohl). 27, D. orthum sp. nov. 28, D. frater sp. nov., arrow: ramellus. 29, hind wing, dorsal, D. curtuvenatum sp. nov., Holotype. 30–33, fore and hind wings, dorsal. 30, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 31, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 32, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 33, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 26 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Metasoma: T1 apical margin with central semicircular mark light brown; apical margin of T2 and 3 often whitish; sternites medially white; ovipositor sheath dark brown, except basal 0.6 ventrally whitish; ovipositor brown (144, 088, 056).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFD1FFB1E6BEA6EEB08137A3" blockId="34.[151,1437,151,1580]" box="[199,392,943,968]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
